glosses.gloss: Marine polyps that resemble flowers but have oral rings of tentacles; differ from corals in forming no hard skeleton
Sea anemones are a group of marine, predatory animals of the order Actiniaria.
Common name for a group of cnidarians
Any of many polyps, of the order Actiniaria, which occurs in marine and estuarine habitats, and which captures its food using tentacles.
